events.name: Offline web apps, Bluetooth LE and two-factor auth
events.description:
We’re back from our summer break and we have some exciting news!

We have Erik Hellman visiting us and he is a Google Developer Expert (GDE)! Erik will have not one but two talks. In one of them he’ll show us how to bring offline capabilities to webapps using Service Workers API and in the other he’ll share his experience with using Bluetooth LE peripherals and APIs on Android.

In addition we have Harri Kirik from Mobilab talking about two-factor authentication on mobile.

Who or what is a Google Developer Expert (GDE)? GDEs are recognized experts in Google technologies who are actively engaging with the community. The program is run by Google and is similar to Java Champions in the Java world and the Most Valuable Professional program in the Microsoft ecosystem.

It is a rare chance to see a GDE speaking right here in Tartu so best not to miss it!

The event takes place on 3rd of August at 18:00 in the Mobilab office (Akadeemia 3).

events.name: Flutter Live Viewing Party with GDG Tartu
events.description:
Google has been working on Flutter for some time now. And we all have wondered - why is there a need for another Android and iOS development SDK? We do already have so many to choose from, don’t we? Well, there are a lot of theories and questions ..

Is it a backup for the frightening situation when the court case with Oracle goes really bad? Or maybe a way to future-proof development on Android and to make the eventual transition to Google Fuchsia? But then, what exactly is this mysterious Fuchsia OS code on GitHub that Google just dumped there and has made no official announcements about whatsoever?

We also do not know.

But seems Google is ready to share more. They will host a Flutter Live 2018 event and live stream it for everyone. Finally!

Since we’re talking about app development, it is only natural we watch the broadcast at the official Google Developers Agency tribe at Mobi Lab. Join us in Mobi Lab Tartu office (Akadeemia Street 3, 2nd floor) on 4th of December. Doors open 18:00, key note starts at 19:00.
We’ll have drinks, snacks, and most importantly - a chance to network with some fellow Google & technology fans.

events.name: Back to school with machine learning, AI, and your new favorite D&D pair
events.description:
The new school year is upon us, so these last days of summer are the right time to warm up your brains a little. Join us on August 28th at Mobi Lab for two short, but fabulous (just like Oleg, one of the GDG Tartu organizers) sessions about machine learning and the power of AI.

We’ll start with a session by Dav, a co-Founder at GreenflyAI, about a smarter approach to AI. Dav will talk about the pros and cons of using off-the-shelf vs. self-development solutions for machine learning.
In the battle of AutoML or AWS Comprehend and similar solutions vs. Tensorflow or PyTorch or TF-Hub and alikes which side should you choose?

Our second speaker, Dima, looks into the latest groundbreaking medical innovations driven by deep learning and evaluates their potential impact on medical practice. He will discuss the main challenges that deep learning engineers face and recent advances that have been proposed in deep learning in order to solve these.

The meetup takes place on August 28th at the Mobi Lab office (Akadeemia Street 3, 2nd floor) at 19:00. Our doors will be open from 18:30. Please let us know if you are coming and RSVP at Meetup.com so we can plan ahead.

The event is hosted and drinks are provided by our friends at Mobi Lab

Speakers
Dav Højt, a co-Founder at GreenflyAI, where they use AI to monitor and improve customer experience, would share his expertise on Machine learning on whether you are better using an off-the-shelf ML solution of should figure out how to implement one yourself.

The one and only Dmytro Fishman will explore the question of are we there yet with the AI doctors, is it ready to change healthcare as we know it and how far can we take the machine learning approaches in medicine.

events.name: GraalVM workshop
events.description:
The last days of December. The last days of the year 2019. The last days of the decade! You thought we're done? Not even close!
You've been waiting, you've been making jokes, you've been wondering whether or not it's a long-running prank. Very soon you'll have the chance to resolve all these burning questions.

December 18th, at Mobispace at Akadeemia 3. Join us for the unprecedented workshop-style GDG Tartu event. Grab your laptop and dive into the wonderful world of new possibilities for building cool new applications with GraalVM. Learn with Oleg about what you can do with it, try it on your applications and discover its beauty! Get amazed by how your Java code can compete in having the ms startup times with native apps without making you reinvent generics every single time!

Build polyglot apps by mixing dynamic languages like you actually can pick the best tool for the job rather than the best tool in your language ecosystem. Python, Ruby, R, JavaScipt, WebAssembly, you'd think it'll quickly become an unmanageable mess guaranteeing you job security for centuries to come. Be amazed how the common tooling can help you debug even the most complicated polyglot apps with breeze.

Or just start the benchmarks and hang out with your peers waiting for the results. How many cups of coffee can you drink while you code computes the first 10^100 prime numbers? Join us and let's find out? *

*We don't actually have that much coffee, we have soft drinks and water.

The event is hosted by Mobispace and drinks are provided by our friends at Mobi Lab

PS. this is an exclusive event, spots are limited, hurry up and really, people, we absolutely need you to bring your laptops. Preferably Linux, or Mac, or Windows with WLS or Docker, or some cloud.
